methods.intSize:
**Incompatible overloads text - text from the first overload:**


 Returns size() cast to an int, if this can be done without losing precision. Otherwise, throws
 SizeException.

*Overload 1*  
  :return: (int) size(), cast to an int
  
*Overload 2*  
  :param operation: (java.lang.String) - A description of the operation that requires an int size
  :return: (int) size(), cast to an int
  
*Overload 3*  
  :param operation: (java.lang.String) - A description of the operation that requires an int size
  :param size: (long) - The size
  :return: (int) size, cast to an int
